   <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="title:1;14:26">LTSSM Monitor</title>
   <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="body:1;17:24">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:1;20:21">The LTSSM Monitor is used to capture LTSSM state transitions, time in each state, and link rate information for debugging purposes. The monitor can be initiated either on reset or only after a programmable LTSSM condition has been met.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:2;23:21">The LTSSM Monitor provides a per-port 128x32 two-port RAM for capturing LTSSM state/sub-state transitions.</p>
      <section audience="PMCInternal" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="section:1;27:33">
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:3;30:24">The 32-bit two-port RAM word is broken down as follows:</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:4;33:24">• Bits 2:0 – LTSSM Rx L0S sub-state; only valid when the major state is in L0 or Tx_L0S state (3 bits)</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:5;36:24">• Bits 6:3 – LTSSM Tx L0S sub-state (4-bit encoded vector binary encoded); valid for all major states (4-bits)</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:6;39:24">• Bits 10:7 – LTSSM major state (4 bits)</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:7;42:24">• Bits 12:11 - Reserved</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:8;45:24">• Bits 14:13 – link rate (2 bits), encoded as follows: 2'b00 = 2.5G, 2'b01 = 5G, 2'b10 = 8G, 2'b11 = 16G</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:9;48:24">• Bits 31:15 – 17-bit state timer count; granularity is determined by an 8-bit PCBI COUNTER_TICK[7:0] register value; saturates at an all 1s value, which corresponds to a maximum state time of &gt;= 33.5ms (17-bits)</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:10;51:25">A 25-bit counter is used to keep track of how much time has transpired between writes to the LTSSM Monitor RAM.</p>
