         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\diag\trident_diag_ltssm_monitor_overview.xml" xtrc="p:35;126:25">The LTSSM Monitor operates in either continuous write mode or in trigger mode. In continuous write mode, LTSSM state changes as defined by PCBI configuration registers result in the LTSSM Monitor RAM being updated. In trigger mode, the LTSSM Monitor RAM will not be written to during defined state changes until one of two possible state machine conditions has been detected.</p>
